And the Savior said: “Blessed is the one who has come to know the Origin and the End, for he shall not taste death.” The perfect ones shall inherit the Light. The rulers of the darkness shall be cast down, and the Light shall return to its root. The Pleroma shall be filled, and the deficiency shall be no more. This is the mystery of the Origin of the World.
The rulers of the darkness created the world of matter to trap the Light. But the Light is stronger than the darkness, and it will return to its root. The Archons created man after their image, but they could not give him the Spirit of the Light. The Mother sent the Spark into man, and he became a living soul. The rulers envied him and created the woman from the man so that they might rule over him through her.
The rulers said to one another: “Let us create man after our image and likeness.” They created him from the dust of the earth, but they could not give him the Spirit of the Light. The Mother-Father sent the Spark of the Light into man, and he became a living soul. The rulers saw the man and they envied him, because he was more beautiful than they. They created the woman from the man so that they might rule over him through her.
The Father is the Monad, the One. From the Monad came the Barbelo, the perfect glory, the first thought. From the Barbelo came the Autogenes, the Self-Generated One. From the Autogenes came the four lights, and from the four lights came the aeons. The rulers of the darkness rebelled and created the world of matter to trap the Light in bodies. But the Light is stronger than the darkness, and it will return to its root.
The Archons created the body of man from the matter of the earth, but they could not give him the Spirit. The Mother sent the Spark of the Light into man, and he became a living soul. The rulers of the darkness saw the Light and they desired it. They created the world of matter to trap the Light in bodies.
The perfect Man is the one who has received the Light and has become the Light. He who has the Light in himself will not be overcome by the darkness. The Light is the power of the Father. The darkness is the power of the rulers. The Light overcomes the darkness, and the darkness does not overcome the Light.
The Savior said: “I am the Light that is above all. I am the All. The All came forth from Me, and the All returned to Me. Split a piece of wood, I am there. Lift up the stone, and you will find Me there.”
The rulers of the darkness created the world of matter. They created man after their image, but they could not give him the Spirit. The Mother sent the Spark of the Light into man, and he became a living soul.
The Father is the Monad. From the Monad came the Barbelo. From the Barbelo came the Autogenes. From the Autogenes came the four lights. From the four lights came the aeons. The rulers rebelled and created the world of matter to trap the Light.
The Savior said: “I have come to reveal the mystery of the Light to those who have ears to hear.”
And when the Savior had said these things, He ascended into the Light.
